Police in Nairobi are hunting for a businessman in whose compound a stolen truck was found. Head of Special Crimes Prevention Unit Noah Katumo said they have obtained an arrest warrant for James Kioi, said to own a godown in Ruai, where the lorry was found.The lorry was reported stolen while transporting cement worth Sh135,000 to Nyandarua last Friday. It was tracked to the compound a day later.Katumo said police sealed off a second godown in Chokaa, also said to be owned by Kioi. Detectives found a spirits manufacturing plant.Three of Kioi s workers were found in the two yards. Last evening, police called in KRA officers after it emerged some of the brands manufactured in the godown could be fake and unregistered.